<br>
After thinking it over a bit, I've come to 1 conclusion which I'm sticking with. As I said before, I was not 100% decided on my course of action. Afterall, why respect people's camps when they don't respect yours? It in no way has anything to do personally, for whichever cleric is currently camping RF. I'm using people as an all encompassing term. However, up to this day I still have never ks'd anyone, and I don't expect to. That being said, this is what will happen, at least as far as my epic is concerned. No one needs to fear being ks'd by my team, whoever may be in it, IF YOU ARE ENGAGED WITH SUFFICIENT FORCE TO DOWN HIM.<br>
<br>
If Ragefire pops, and I know about it, expect my team on the way. If my team is the first there, before the team for cleric camping it, you get 1 half hour from the time I get to the spawn, to get your people there, and 1 chance. Now thats speaking rather loosely, I might not find out RF is up for an hour after he pops, that gives you an hour and a half, thats more than *most* teams will give you. If your team is there in the allotted time, and engages, and DOES NOT WIPE, I will congratulate you on a job well done, and return another spawn. However, if you do wipe, I WILL finish the dragon. As sage said, guilds aren't charities, if you start to founder, do not expect my or my team's help. If my team is NOT the first there, you have as many chances as you can fit in, until I do get there, in which case, the above rule applies, 30 minutes from the time I get there, and 1 chance. That is provided some other guild decides you won't be able to kill it and snakes it out from under you, to keep it from despawning.<br>
<br>
It sounds harsh, but in the end, it does EQUAL my respecting the camp. Do whatever quoting or bashing you choose Kav. It also means that I expect and ACCEPT the same treatment from the other cleric teams needing Rage, on the far out chance I decide to subject myself to camping that insane spawn again.<br>
<br>
Drae <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukavaren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kavaren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/2/02 12:11:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is RF a camp or FFA! Need some advice</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So you attack my method of doing things Kav. Typical, its not what you would if you had the camp, and thats understandable. But don't even fucking start on the idea that I didn't put forth the effort before. If you for one second think I'm the only cleric who got chased out of the lair, you are sadly mistaken. So I don't ask for outside help to clear fgs? So? That doesn't mean I didn't put the effort in. ANY cleric who camped solb previously, and now insists on camping the SF version, put in effort. You don't like the idea? Tough shit. Maybe you are the type who thinks the guild should do the camp work FOR the cleric, heh, sorry, I don't think that way either. Still doesn't mean I didn't put forth effort.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
